Package org.goplanit.osm.tags

Class OsmPedestrianTags

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.goplanit.osm.tags.OsmPedestrianTags
  • public class OsmPedestrianTags
extends Object
    pedestrian related tags which are not really grouped in a logical way in OSM, hence we provide all of them here as well as some convenience methods to quickly collect some of the most relevant ones. For the mode "foot" see also OsmRoadModeTags
    Author:
    markr

      • getOsmPedestrianKeyTags

        public static final String[] getOsmPedestrianKeyTags()
        collect set of key tags that signify specific pedestrian configurations. Currently:
        • sidewalk
        • foot
        • footway
        • pedestrian
        Returns:
        unmodifiable set of pedestrian related key tags

      • hasExplicitSidewalkOrFootwayWithAccessValue

                                                                  String... accessValueTags)

        Parameters:

        accessValueTags - to consider
        Returns:
        true when one or more of the tag values is found, false otherwise

      • hasExplicitlyIncludedSidewalkOrFootway

        public static boolean hasExplicitlyIncludedSidewalkOrFootway​(Map<String,​String> tags)
        Verify from the passed in tags if a side walk or footway is present that is accessible to pedestrians sidewalk=
        • yes
        • both
        • left
        • right
        or footway=sidewalk
        Parameters:
        tags - to verify
        Returns:
        true when explicitly mentioned and available, false otherwise (could still support pedestrians if highway type suports it by default)
